content.text: ElizaOS and @ai16zdao/@elizaOS have seen significant growth over the past two weeks. The project has now reached over 14.4k stars on GitHub (+600), 4.5k forks (+400), and 508 contributors (+23).
A new update has been made to the Trusted Execution Environment (TEE) in ElizaOS. The update includes various improvements and fixes, though specific details are not provided in the PR description.
The main branch of ElizaOS has been synchronized with Jobsy, ensuring that the latest updates and improvements are integrated.

A security update has been applied to the Vitest dependency in ElizaOS. This update addresses CVE-2025-24964, which could allow remote code execution via Cross-site WebSocket hijacking (CSWSH) attacks. The update moves Vitest from version 1.4.0 to 1.6.1 and 2.1.8 to 2.1.9.
A version bump and lockfile update have been made to ElizaOS, ensuring that dependencies are up to date and stable.
@shawmakesmagic has been hacked. Users are advised not to interact with the account's tweets. Additionally, there are no $elizaOS tokens being distributed.
The elizaOS roadmap has been released, outlining short-term, mid-term, and long-term goals for all products in the ecosystem.
Development on elizaOS v2 continues, with Shaw working on a multi-agent program that assigns roles to agents for community management.

No WDYGDTW update this week as new formats are being considered. Instead, a highlight on elizaOS agents on other chains: TalosAgent on Cardano by FluxPoint Studio, which focuses on portfolio management, token risk analysis, and market making.

A bug in the advanced-sdk-ts import makes it impossible to correctly add @elizaos/agent to new projects due to an indirect dependency on @elizaos/plugin-coinbase. The issue has been reported on GitHub.

categories.title: Recent Fixes and Enhancements in Eliza OS

content.text: A fix was implemented to add a default voice for ElevenLabs in Eliza OS.
A fix was made to address an issue with Discord testing in Eliza OS.

A bug fix was applied to resolve a vector dimension mismatch error in the `plugin-news` module. The system now ensures that memory entries have a valid embedding format by using `getEmbeddingZeroVector()`. This change improves memory management in Eliza OS.

A user encountered a transcription error in the Discord plugin after installing ffmpeg. The error occurs when the system attempts to access the SQLite database, resulting in a 'TypeError: The database connection is not open'. Assistance is requested to resolve this issue.

A new plugin prototype, 'plugin-extractor', has been introduced to integrate with the Extractor Agent Firewall API. This plugin allows passing an agent's character profile and messages for risk scoring. If the risk score exceeds a threshold, messaging or agent deployment can be blocked. Core framework guidance is required for proper rejection flow.

A refactor of the 'Plugin Local AI' has been initiated. The update includes local inference via deepseek R1, removal of unsupported elements, and the introduction of a process manager. TTS now utilizes the OuteTTS model, and improvements have been made to prevent JSON issues. Further testing and code cleanup are ongoing.

KaiTravelAI, built on Buk Protocol, is an AI agent designed to plan complete travel itineraries. It is particularly useful for crypto enthusiasts attending global conventions.

A documentation update in the ElizaOS project corrects branch naming conventions in CONTRIBUTING.md. The change replaces a double hyphen (`--`) with a single hyphen (`-`) for better alignment with Git standards.

categories.title: Latest Updates: Agent Marketplace, DegenAI, AIXVC, and ElizaOS v0.25.7 Release

content.text: Updates for the agent marketplace (launchpad), DegenAI, and AIXVC (PMAIRCA) have been released, including version 2 updates.
ElizaOS v0.25.7 has been released, incorporating multiple changes and improvements. The changelog includes updates from various pull requests such as #3339, #3343, #3344, and more.

categories.title: Client Shows Blank Page and Errors

content.text: A user reported an issue where the Eliza client displays a blank page and logs errors in the browser console. The error message indicates that the requested module 'react-router.js' does not provide an export named 'NavLink'. Additionally, network errors such as 'ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED' and 'ERR_NETWORK_IO_SUSPENDED' were observed.

A recent pull request introduced an environment variable `SERVER_URL` to replace hardcoded references to 'http://localhost'. This change allows users to configure the client to connect to a different server, such as a home lab setup. The update ensures that network requests use the specified `SERVER_URL` instead of assuming a local server.
